      The city of Buenos Aires has two airports. Aeropuerto Internacional Ministro Pistarni (Ezeiza), serves international flights, and Aeroparque Jorge Newbery (Aeroparque), serves domestic and regional flights. The cost of taxi (car service, which is also called Remise) from Ezeiza to downtown Buenos Aires is 45 pesos and takes approximately 45 minutes. Aeroparque is very close to downtown,&nbsp;it takes 15 minutes to get to the airport from downtown and costs 13 pesos by taxi.&nbsp; From Ezeiza,&nbsp;Manuel Tienda León Bus Company&nbsp;has frequent bus service to the&nbsp;city center, which costs about 16 pesos.&nbsp;If you really&nbsp;want to go budget with transporation and are not carrying a large luggage, public transportation costs 1.35 pesos but takes&nbsp;almost 2 hours. &nbsp; &nbsp;  You can also find ferry and hydrofoil services in Buenos Aires to and from Uruguay. The ferry to Montevideo/Colonial leaves from Puerto Madero and also Tigre at regular intervals and costs 45-95 pesos.  &nbsp;  The main bus terminal in Buenos Aires is Retiro and here you can find a bus to go anywhere in Argentina and most places in the region.&nbsp;Here you can find the main private bus companies in the region and frequent service. &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;   
    


